name: Channeling (Tlalocan series)
description: Channeling refers to when a person's body is being taken over by a spirit for the purpose of communication.Tlalocan is described in Aztec manuscripts as a paradise, reserved for those who had drowned or had otherwise been killed by manifestations of water, such as by flood or in storms by strikes. It is authentic digital work created by using my monochromatic painting as a model.
